Class ConnectionTracker

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.commonreality.reality.impl.handler.ConnectionTracker
  • Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public class ConnectionTracker
extends java.lang.Object
    class that tracks which connection credentials we will accept as well as assigns, links and accesses IParticipantIdentifiers and IAddressingInformation

    This is now deprecated in favor of StateAndConnectionManager

        check to see if the connection should be accepted based on the credentials. If it is to be accepted, the connection will be accepted provisionally and an IIdentifier will be assigned to the participant. The connection is not officially connected, however, until authorizeConnection(IIdentifier, ICredentials) is called.
